To modify the negative test case and include the collection failure scenario, you can update the test case as follows:

void givenOutputFilePathNotAccessible() {
  spaceCollector.setUrl("192.168.1.243");
  spaceCollector.setPort(8080);
  spaceCollector.setUserName("custom");
  spaceCollector.setPassword("sshcolletor");
  spaceCollector.setInputFilePath("C:/Temp/sampleMeasInfoData.xml");
  spaceCollector.setOutputFilePath("");

  assertFalse(sshExceptionHandler.outputFilepathNotAccessible(spaceCollector));

  // Update the condition to check if the job status is COLLECTION_FAILED
  assertEquals(JobStatus.COLLECTION_FAILED.toString(), auditQueueMap.get("job_status"));
}

By including the condition to check if the job status is COLLECTION_FAILED, you can ensure that the new format of Unified Audit Message is published to the 3459-DEV-COLLECTION-AUDIT-QUEUE.